        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "An agent appraisal estimates what a motivated buyer would pay in a competitive open market campaign. A bank valuation, commissioned by a lender, asks what the property would sell for in a distressed or forced sale. Bank valuers weight confirmed historical sales and apply a conservative, repeatable methodology. This structural difference is why a bank valuation routinely comes in below an agent appraisal. Neither number is wrong. They are answering different questions."
      }
